-- India cbank says to conduct 21-day term repo auction for 500 bln rupees on Friday
-- By Neha Dasgupta
-- Tue Mar 11, 2014 09:28AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, March 11 (Reuters) - The Reserve Bank of India will conduct a 21-day term repo variable rate auction for 500 billion rupees ($8.21 billion) on March 14, it said on Tuesday.

The RBI will not conduct any term repo auction on March 18 when the existing term repo of 300.04 billion rupees matures, it said.